Camel milk tastes very similar to cow milk. It does have a distinctive taste - slightly salty, but also smooth, refreshing, and fulfilling. Some are surprised when they first drink it, as they learn that it isn't nearly as off-putting as one might expect.

((This is a Job System Item.))
